WAAVP Sample Sizes

This document shows the (currently) proposed sample sizes and mean egg counts that we are considering. The recommendations are designed so that the probability of a conclusive result (i.e.equivalent of the study power) is >= 80% (black horizontal line) for all values of population efficacy above the Target (green line/dots) and below Target-Delta (red line/dots). In between Target-Delta and Target is the grey zone where we accept that it is unlikely that we can make a definitive conclusion.

To look at the effect of tweaking these parameters see the online app here
